POLICE have arrested a former principal for allegedly raping a 15-year-old girl in Lorraine village in Sekororo last week. Limpopo police spokesperson colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the former principal allegedly told the girl he wanted to give her a message."Subsequently, he took her to his home in Loraine village where on arrival he raped her," Ngoepe said.The pupil opened a case and the suspect was later arrested, he said.He appeared briefly at Lenyenye Magistrate's court on Monday afternoon. He is due to appear again on Tuesday morning.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/principal-arrested-for-alleged-rape-of-teen-pupil-20170619